(46, 1, '2022-08-19 08:46:20', '2022-08-19 08:46:20', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Life update: Studying teaching. Feeling unsure. Have always seen that system as an oppressive one. Do I want to be part of it. Have been feeling bad for giving up all design and creative related things. But will finish the semester and see how I go. I just want to take care of myself and contribute a bit, without struggling so damn much like I have been doing in the last five years in design. Still generally confused. This website however will be refocused as a creative expression, an experiment in all types of art. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":47,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-4-1024x681.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-47\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Grain</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Fuji Acros simulation includes it\'s own neat grain formula - so you can turn the grain off in Image Settings. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":45,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-45\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":40,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-40\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shooting with high ISO emphasizes the grain, at the expense of dynamic range and resolution I guess. To increase the ISO to ridiculous levels, you need to reduce the amount of incoming light. Use a ND filter, if you have one (the x100 line all have one built in!). If not, you can crank up the aperture. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":41,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-2-1024x681.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-41\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>High contrast</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can use the tone curve in Image Settings to increase the contrast of the image. To keep a little of the dynamic range though, you can set DR to 400. I don\'t worry too much about blowing out the highlights anymore, as long as it looks natural. Of course I try not to (but not </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":38,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-1024x683.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-38\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Fujifilm Acros Simulation Tips', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '37-autosave-v1', '', '', '2022-08-19 08:46:20', '2022-08-19 08:46:20', '', 37, 'http://alidarkssg/?p=46', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
