(48, 1, '2022-08-19 08:44:27', '2022-08-19 08:44:27', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Life update: Studying teaching. Feeling unsure. Have always seen that system as an oppressive one. Do I want to be part of it. Have been feeling bad for giving up all design and creative related things. But will finish the semester and see how I go. I just want to take care of myself and contribute a bit, without struggling so damn much like I have been doing in the last five years in design. Still generally confused. This website however will be refocused as a creative expression, an experiment in all types of art. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":47,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-4-1024x681.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-47\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":38,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-1024x683.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-38\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Grain</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Fuji Acros simulation includes it\'s own neat grain formula - so you can turn the grain off in Image Settings. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":45,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-45\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":40,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-40\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shooting with high ISO emphasizes the grain, at the expense of dynamic range and resolution I guess. To increase the ISO to ridiculous levels, you need to reduce the amount of incoming light. Use a ND filter, if you have one (the x100 line all have one built in!). If not, you can crank up the aperture. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":41,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-2-1024x681.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-41\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Fujifilm Acros Simulation Tips', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-08-19 08:44:27', '2022-08-19 08:44:27', '', 37, 'http://alidarkssg/?p=48', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(49, 1, '2022-08-19 08:46:38', '2022-08-19 08:46:38', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Life update: Studying teaching. Feeling unsure. Have always seen that system as an oppressive one. Do I want to be part of it. Have been feeling bad for giving up all design and creative related things. But will finish the semester and see how I go. I just want to take care of myself and contribute a bit, without struggling so damn much like I have been doing in the last five years in design. Still generally confused. This website however will be refocused as a creative expression, an experiment in all types of art. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":47,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-4-1024x681.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-47\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Grain</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Fuji Acros simulation includes it\'s own neat grain formula - so you can turn the grain off in Image Settings. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":45,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-45\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":40,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-40\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shooting with high ISO emphasizes the grain, at the expense of dynamic range and resolution I guess. To increase the ISO to ridiculous levels, you need to reduce the amount of incoming light. Use a ND filter, if you have one (the x100 line all have one built in!). If not, you can crank up the aperture. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":41,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-2-1024x681.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-41\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>High contrast</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can use the tone curve in Image Settings to increase the contrast of the image. To keep a little of the dynamic range though, you can set DR to 400. I don\'t worry too much about blowing out the highlights anymore, as long as it looks natural. Of course I try not to, but all my photos are JPEG so there\'s usually a little extra clipping.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":38,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-1024x683.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-38\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Fujifilm Acros Simulation Tips', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-08-19 08:46:38', '2022-08-19 08:46:38', '', 37, 'http://alidarkssg/?p=49', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(50, 1, '2022-08-21 04:48:15', '2022-08-21 04:48:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I got into taking photos in 2015, I started writing about the journey on Medium. Here are the best of those:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/click-the-shutter/please-don-t-call-it-art-7ca3e1c7ca8c\">Please Don\'t Call it Art</a> - 2015</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/click-the-shutter/going-jpeg-1651f9779690\">Going JPEG</a> - 2015</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/click-the-shutter/stop-editing-and-shoot-e0076d82e19e\">How Apple Photos Helps Me Enjoy Photography Again</a> - 2015</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/@alidark3000/iphone-11-does-mie-japan-52a69cf3031f\">iPhone 11 does Mie, Japan</a> - 2019</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":51,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alidarkssg/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/vsco5dbbe53e92125-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-51\"/><figcaption>Nagoya strolling</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Some early essays on photography', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'some-early-essays-on-photography', '', '', '2022-08-21 04:48:15', '2022-08-21 04:48:15', '', 0, 'http://alidarkssg/?p=50', 0, 'post', '', 0),
